- Enough!
- Don't tell me how to fight the ship!

15:41.916 --> 15:43.276
Keep lobbing missiles like that,

15:43.356 --> 15:45.116
and they're gonna knock
them down every time!

15:45.156 --> 15:46.852
- They're low on missiles. They have to be!
- So are we!

15:46.876 --> 15:48.996
They're not gonna shoot at
us while we have the seeds.

15:49.299 --> 15:51.679
Use the damn advantage and charge them!

15:51.954 --> 15:53.310
Charge them!

15:53.459 --> 15:54.479
♪

15:55.111 --> 15:56.943
I've got a lock on Vellek's ship.

15:58.551 --> 15:59.811
Heading straight for us.

15:59.911 --> 16:02.571
They're tired of missing.
Lucia wants a fistfight.

16:02.671 --> 16:03.931
She knows we can't fire back.

16:04.031 --> 16:05.770
Might as well get within potato range.

16:06.364 --> 16:09.104
Gator, set course for Linosa.
We need the island cover.

16:09.129 --> 16:11.309
Hardly a fair fight. We can't fire.

16:11.484 --> 16:13.309
So we knock the fight out of them.

16:15.589 --> 16:17.303
Let them chase us around the island.

16:17.404 --> 16:20.584
But drop a couple operators
in a zodiac right in her path.

16:20.640 --> 16:22.144
Board and cripple that ship.

16:22.244 --> 16:24.380
<i>Nathan James</i> can then
come out of cover and take control

16:24.404 --> 16:25.904
while we find the seeds.

16:26.472 --> 16:28.145
We still have to exfil our operators.

16:28.170 --> 16:29.682
From the sound of it,
they're not in any shape...

16:29.706 --> 16:30.746
I'll go.

16:30.970 --> 16:32.564
It's personal for Lucia.

16:32.957 --> 16:34.730
They have the seeds. She wants me.

16:37.470 --> 16:38.716
If I fail,

16:39.387 --> 16:41.277
<i>Nathan James</i> lives to fight another day.

16:41.701 --> 16:42.741
I'll go with you.

16:44.132 --> 16:45.683
It's personal for me, too.

16:45.901 --> 16:51.101
♪

16:51.850 --> 16:54.190
[OBJECTS CLATTER]

16:56.605 --> 16:59.092
Dad, that's just distilled
Nostos for plants.

16:59.123 --> 17:01.283
It'll mellow you out, but
it won't bring Christos back.

17:02.165 --> 17:03.545
What did you do with it?

17:03.570 --> 17:04.711
What did you do with my damn stash?

17:04.712 --> 17:05.809
I dumped it.

17:06.570 --> 17:07.872
Oh, my God.

17:08.192 --> 17:10.291
I need you sharp. You're a junkie,

17:10.392 --> 17:12.734
and your recklessness got Giorgio killed.

17:12.876 --> 17:14.892
And now you want the
rest of us to join him.

17:16.073 --> 17:17.592
I won't let that happen.

17:17.913 --> 17:20.050
From now on, we do this my way or...

17:20.075 --> 17:21.320
- [SLAPS]
- Oh!

17:23.858 --> 17:25.093
[WHIMPERS]

17:25.193 --> 17:31.973
♪

17:34.789 --> 17:36.462
I'm not angry at you, Dad.

17:36.989 --> 17:38.408
Not anymore.

17:38.869 --> 17:40.793
Anger won't bring my brothers back.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.473
Christos, stop her.

17:46.636 --> 17:48.109
He doesn't leave the lab.

17:50.072 --> 17:51.170
Christos.

17:52.964 --> 17:54.121
Christos.

17:55.316 --> 17:56.433
Christos?

17:58.132 --> 17:59.284
Christos?

17:59.996 --> 18:01.451
[MUTTERS] Christos...

18:03.171 --> 18:04.831
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

18:04.931 --> 18:07.606
<i>Nathan James</i> will maintain
position behind the island.

18:07.845 --> 18:09.665
First, you'll need to burn the ship's radar

18:09.765 --> 18:11.061
by crippling its cooling mechanism.

18:11.085 --> 18:12.905
Cooling skid's in the engine room. Got it.

18:13.005 --> 18:14.765
When it goes, you'll have a couple minutes

18:14.845 --> 18:17.145
before the radar systems
auto-shutdown from the heat.

18:17.245 --> 18:19.625
- No radar, no targeting.
- Understood.

18:19.725 --> 18:21.905
Compromising the engine's reduction gear

18:22.005 --> 18:23.865
will grind the ship's propulsion to a halt.

18:24.445 --> 18:25.585
It's usually padlocked.

18:25.685 --> 18:26.901
All you gotta do is gum up the works.

18:26.925 --> 18:27.949
Not a problem.

18:28.454 --> 18:30.754
Now we won't make a move
until we know you guys are DIW.

18:30.853 --> 18:33.273
So if <i>anything</i> goes south, bail,

18:33.373 --> 18:35.069
and we will come around
and we will pick you up...

18:35.093 --> 18:37.287
Captain. We got it.

18:37.933 --> 18:38.993
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

18:39.684 --> 18:41.910
Yeah. I can see that.

18:42.746 --> 18:43.766
Good luck.

18:43.866 --> 18:50.822
♪

18:53.466 --> 18:56.726
