35:44.901 --> 35:46.721
[GASPING]

35:46.821 --> 35:48.122
[WHISPERS] Daddy?

35:48.701 --> 35:49.799
Daddy...

35:50.141 --> 35:52.521
♪

35:53.181 --> 35:55.735
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

35:56.661 --> 36:01.081
♪

36:01.831 --> 36:02.831
This world...

36:03.772 --> 36:05.616
Somewhere, this world is good.

36:06.012 --> 36:12.632
♪

36:12.732 --> 36:14.999
Step away from the edge, Vellek.

36:17.433 --> 36:19.079
I offered a cure, man.

36:19.633 --> 36:22.879
A real and final cure for
the sickness in us all.

36:23.818 --> 36:25.686
You of all people should know about that...

36:26.088 --> 36:28.049
what you've seen, what you've done.

36:28.428 --> 36:30.267
You need what I'm
offering more than anybody.

36:30.348 --> 36:31.802
You're right, Doctor.

36:32.508 --> 36:34.368
I have seen the worst in people,

36:34.851 --> 36:36.758
the worst in myself.

36:38.044 --> 36:39.824
But I've also seen strength in others

36:39.924 --> 36:41.413
that you wouldn't believe,

36:42.433 --> 36:44.716
and kindness that would bring you to tears.

36:46.404 --> 36:47.624
That was beautiful, man.

36:47.724 --> 36:49.140
I can clearly see why people follow you.

36:49.164 --> 36:50.544
But you are the one-eyed king.

36:50.644 --> 36:53.315
I offer you peace, you choose war.

36:53.581 --> 36:55.634
Peace at the cost of free will?

36:56.181 --> 36:57.801
I'll take war anytime.

36:57.901 --> 36:59.210
[SIGHS]

36:59.861 --> 37:03.441
"We the people"...
Addicted to your darkness.

37:04.205 --> 37:07.081
Being human isn't about
cutting out the darkness.

37:08.491 --> 37:10.050
It's about fighting,

37:10.372 --> 37:13.490
every day, to find the light!

37:13.591 --> 37:20.211
♪

37:21.537 --> 37:23.004
No, Captain.

37:23.264 --> 37:24.964
♪

37:24.998 --> 37:27.657
You don't have to fight to find the light.

37:28.449 --> 37:30.376
Give the world another chance.

37:30.970 --> 37:32.604
See the good for yourself.

37:33.157 --> 37:34.817
The people still need you.

37:35.385 --> 37:38.123
We have the seeds, but
we need your science.

37:38.837 --> 37:41.937
♪

37:42.445 --> 37:44.485
I appreciate the invite, man.

37:45.277 --> 37:47.857
♪

37:48.817 --> 37:49.892
But there's Heaven.

37:49.917 --> 37:53.177
♪

37:54.169 --> 37:55.332
And I gotta go.

37:55.357 --> 38:01.911
♪

38:06.999 --> 38:14.977
♪

38:17.671 --> 38:20.951
♪

38:34.663 --> 38:36.983
- [MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]
- ♪

38:37.008 --> 38:38.008
[GLOVE SNAPS]

38:38.084 --> 38:40.504
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

38:40.529 --> 38:42.176
[WHISPERS] Hi, sweetheart.

38:42.329 --> 38:45.843
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

38:46.929 --> 38:48.731
[EXHALES] You did it.

38:49.649 --> 38:52.469
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

38:52.933 --> 38:54.560
You saved the world again.

38:54.929 --> 38:56.269
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

38:56.369 --> 38:58.629
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

38:59.912 --> 39:01.028
Easy day.

39:01.554 --> 39:02.726
[CHUCKLES]

39:02.969 --> 39:03.969
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

39:04.009 --> 39:07.377
[MONITOR BEEPING STEADILY]

39:08.289 --> 39:14.669
♪

39:16.510 --> 39:18.230
SLATTERY: We have the
seeds. They look good.

39:18.807 --> 39:20.986
We salvaged what we could
of Vellek's research,

39:22.383 --> 39:25.603
got our hands on some cured
plants that are Nostos free,

39:25.704 --> 39:27.071
and plenty of bugs.

39:28.759 --> 39:31.579
Doc Rios figures we can spread
that cure around the world

39:31.679 --> 39:33.979
in half the time it took
the Red Rust to poison it.

39:34.079 --> 39:37.139
A hell of a stunt you
pulled, ramming that ship.

39:37.239 --> 39:38.603
I've seen crazier.

39:39.879 --> 39:43.019
Anyway, we found a port to
refuel, and we got a-a plane

39:43.044 --> 39:45.325
to evacuate our wounded
as quickly as possible.

39:45.759 --> 39:46.927
Where we headed?

39:47.199 --> 39:49.722
Not far from your old
stomping grounds in Greece.

39:50.590 --> 39:52.245
We're gonna deliver the refugees,

39:52.270 --> 39:54.156
and then you can decide if
you wanna be dropped off, too,

39:54.180 --> 39:55.596
or pick up your family.

39:55.849 --> 39:58.593
I can take you wherever it is
you might want to go to next.

39:59.390 --> 40:01.236
♪

40:01.261 --> 40:02.500
[SIGHS]

40:03.002 --> 40:04.548
How about home?

40:05.310 --> 40:08.730
♪

40:08.830 --> 40:10.518
Yeah, home it is.

40:10.910 --> 40:13.450
♪

40:14.150 --> 40:15.781
So this is what you guys do all day?

40:16.605 --> 40:17.620
Pretty much.

40:17.721 --> 40:19.061
That is something else.

40:19.538 --> 40:21.341
You all giving my man Gator a hard time?

40:21.441 --> 40:24.341
Uh, his testicles just dropped,
so yeah, we're about to start.

40:25.028 --> 40:27.940
Hey, how many navigators does
it take to change a lightbulb?

40:28.285 --> 40:29.369
How many?

40:29.416 --> 40:31.596
One, if you can find it. [LAUGHS]

40:31.696 --> 40:34.038
- [GROANS] Jesus, Miller.
- You just make that up?

40:34.063 --> 40:36.363
- I'm on drugs.
- Doc, up his dosage, please.

40:36.463 --> 40:37.563
Please, cut him off.

40:37.663 --> 40:40.383
[LAUGHTER]

40:46.423 --> 40:52.523
♪

40:53.763 --> 40:55.212
You should be resting.

40:55.829 --> 40:58.079
[SIGHS] Resting doesn't
seem to be my thing.

40:58.104 --> 40:59.104
[CHUCKLES]

40:59.683 --> 41:01.863
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

41:01.963 --> 41:04.663
Well, you saved the world. Again.

41:05.044 --> 41:06.152
<i>We</i> did.

41:06.937 --> 41:08.429
It was always "we."

41:09.598 --> 41:11.434
Let's hope this time it's for good.

41:13.270 --> 41:14.624
Future's uncertain.

41:16.007 --> 41:18.263
Vellek was right. There's
still a lot of bad out there.

41:18.363 --> 41:20.103
♪

41:21.327 --> 41:23.116
But at least we're getting a fresh start.

41:25.407 --> 41:27.660
